    "incident_name": "Customer 360 identity merge job fails on deadlock",
    "category": "Long Running Job Failure",
    "severity": "Sev-1 (Critical)",
    "description": "Long Running Job Failure incident on the Ecommerce pipeline (RTL_ECM_LRJF): customer 360 identity merge job fails on deadlock.",
    "symptoms": "Nightly identity-resolution DAG fails after 4h10m runtime with a Postgres deadlock error on the crosswalk table.",
    "root_cause": "Two concurrent merge tasks (loyalty_merge and guest_merge) both acquire row-level locks on customer_crosswalk in opposite order, producing a classic deadlock.",
    "business_impact": "Customer 360 profile unavailable for the morning CRM refresh; support agents work off stale profiles for ~90 minutes.",
    "resolution": "Enforce a consistent lock-acquisition order between the two merge tasks, or serialize them with a trigger_rule dependency instead of running in parallel."
  },
